All executable programs included in this lab are the following:
// EvaluateCFList.py
// EvaluateCFRandom.py
// cf_core.py
// README

Running EvaluateCFList.py
// expected usage: python3 EvaluateCFList.py Method Filename
// example usage: python3 EvaluateCFList.py 4 test_file.csv
* Method refers to the collaborate filtering method ID, which, in this case is Predict Average KNN
* Filename: CSV file containing test cases
Each line contains of the csv contains: UserID,ItemID



Running EvaluateCFRandom.py
// expected usage: python3 EvaluateCFRandom.py Method Size Repeats
// example usage: python3 EvaluateCFRandom.py 2 50 4
* Method refers to the collaborative filtering method ID, which, in this case is Predict User Pearson KNN
* Size refers to the # of random tests cases in a given run, which is 100 in this case
* Repeats refers to the # of times it is repeated/run, which is 5 in this case

The above programs utilize cf_core.py, a program that:
// loads & parses the dataset
// computes statistics
// implements cosine and pearson correlation similarity functions
// implements predictive collaborative filtering methods
// evaluates predictions using evaluation metrics like MAE

## Implemented Methods

### Method 1: Weighted Sum using Cosine Similarity

### Method 2: Adjusted Weighted N Nearest Neighbors using Pearson Correlation

### Method 3: Weighted N Nearest Neighbors using Cosine Similarity

### Method 4: Average N Nearest Neighbors Ranking